{"title_page": "Nehemiah Blakiston", "text_new": "{{Infobox Governor\n|name= Nehemiah Blakiston \n|image = \n|caption = \n|order =[[List of colonial governors of Maryland|2\u00baLeaders of the Protestant Associators of Maryland]]\n|office = \n|term_start = 1691\n|term_end = 1692\n|predecessor = [[John Coode (Governor of Maryland)|John Coode]]\n|successor = [[Lionel Copley|Sir Lionel Copley]] (1st Royal Governor)\n| birth_name = \n|birth_date  = \n|birth_place =  \n|death_date =\n|death_place = \n|party = \n|profession = colonial governor \n|religion = Puritan Christian\n|relatives = [[Nathaniel Blakiston]], [[John Blakiston]]\n}}\n\n'''Nehemiah Blakiston''' was Governor of the [[Province of Maryland|Maryland colony]] from 1691\u20131692. He became Governor as the '''[[List of colonial governors of Maryland|2nd Leader of the Protestant Associators]]'''., succeeding [[John Coode (Governor of Maryland)|John Coode]], who has taken control of the colony, following the 1688 [[Glorious Revolution]], in England. Blakiston was succeeded by the first Governor with an official royal appointment, [[Lionel Copley]]. He was related to [[Nathaniel Blakiston]].\n\n{{Governors of Maryland}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Blakiston, Nehemiah}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing]]\n[[Category:Year of death missing]]\n[[Category:Kingdom of England emigrants to the Thirteen Colonies]]\n[[Category:Colonial Governors of Maryland]]\n\n{{Maryland-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Governor\n|name= Nehemiah Blakiston \n|image = \n|caption = \n|order =[[List of colonial governors of Maryland|2\u00baLeaders of the Protestant Associators of Maryland]]\n|office = \n|term_start = 1691\n|term_end = 1692\n|predecessor = [[John Coode (Governor of Maryland)|John Coode]]\n|successor = [[Lionel Copley|Sir Lionel Copley]] (1st Royal Governor)\n| birth_name = \n|birth_date  = \n|birth_place =  \n|death_date =\n|death_place = \n|party = \n|profession = colonial governor \n|religion = Puritan Christian\n|relatives = [[Nathaniel Blakiston]], [[John Blakiston]]\n}}\n\n'''Nehemiah Blakiston''' was Governor of the [[Province of Maryland|Maryland colony]] from 1691-1692. He became Governor as the '''[[List of colonial governors of Maryland|2nd Leader of the Protestant Associators]]'''., succeeding [[John Coode (Governor of Maryland)|John Coode]], who has taken control of the colony, following the 1688 [[Glorious Revolution]], in England. Blakiston was succeeded by the first Governor with an official royal appointment, [[Lionel Copley]]. He was related to [[Nathaniel Blakiston]].\n\n{{Governors of Maryland}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Blakiston, Nehemiah}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing]]\n[[Category:Year of death missing]]\n[[Category:Kingdom of England emigrants to the Thirteen Colonies]]\n[[Category:Colonial Governors of Maryland]]\n\n{{Maryland-politician-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: 1691-1692 \u2192 1691\u20131692", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nehemiah_Blakiston"}
